---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Joseph Okonda — Research Engineer at the Broad Institute.">
  <main style="max-width: var(--content-width); margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">About</h1>

    <div class="bio-layout">
      <div class="bio-text">
        <p>
          I'm a Research Engineer at <a href="https://www.broadinstitute.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Broad Institute</a>,
          where I work at the intersection of software engineering and computational biology.
          I design and build tools to process, organize, and analyze data from high throughput single cell sequencing experiments.
        </p>
        <p>
          Previously, I was at <a href="https://www.gsam.com/content/gsam/global/en/homepage.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Goldman Sachs</a>,
          building computational systems in the asset management division.
          I graduated from Stanford with a B.S. in Computer Science.
        </p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
          <li><a href="https://github.com/jlikhuva" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[GitHub]</a></li>
          <li style="margin-top: 0.25rem;"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jlikhuva" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[LinkedIn]</a></li>
          <li style="margin-top: 0.25rem;"><a href={`${base}/cv.pdf`} target="_blank">[CV]</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
          Email: jlikhuva at alumni dot stanford dot edu
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bio-img">
        <img src={`${base}/assets/bio.jpg`} alt="Joseph Okonda" style="border-radius: 4px; max-width: 200px;" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <h2>About the Website</h2>
    <p>
      This website is a mix of three things: a repository of detailed notes I take during personal study,
      a collection of day-to-day unrefined thoughts that seemed interesting at the time (Sketches+Snippets),
      and a collection of refined essays or distillations of ideas (Writing).
    </p>

    <h2>About the Name</h2>
    <p>
      Why Hubris+Humility? To do any meaningful work you have to first believe that you <em>can</em> do
      meaningful work — work that is field-defining. This requires a certain degree of self-confidence.
      This is Hubris. On its own, this belief is not enough. However, when coupled with the ability to
      recognize one's limitations in skill and the patience to systematically remedy those deficiencies —
      this is Humility.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Notable Projects & Research</h2>

    <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem;">
      <div class="project-card">
        <div style="flex: 1;">
          <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.05rem;">Spotting and Transcribing Structured Nutrition Information for Product Images</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0.25rem 0 0.5rem;">Computer Vision · Spring 2018; Updated Summer 2022</p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Back before the era of powerful multimodal AI systems, I designed a system for reading nutrition labels.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/jlikhuva/NutritionProject/blob/master/Data/arxiv.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">[Paper]</a>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/jlikhuva/NutritionProject/blob/master/Data/_poster.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          <img src={`${base}/assets/231.png`} alt="Nutrition project poster" style="max-width: 120px; border-radius: 4px;" data-no-zoom />
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="project-card">
        <div style="flex: 1;">
          <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.05rem;">Building a Robust and Reliable Genomics Data API</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0.25rem 0 0.5rem;">
            Joseph Okonda, Qiuyue Liu, Jared Nedzel, Kristin Ardlie ·
            <a href="https://commonfund.nih.gov/dataecosystem" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NIH CFDE Poster</a>
            · <span style="color: var(--color-accent);">Best Poster Award</span>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Designed and led the implementation of a full genomic data retrieval and exploration API.</p>
          <a href="https://www.gtexportal.org/home/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size: 0.875rem; margin-right: 0.75rem;">[Website]</a>
          <a href="https://gtexportal.org/api/v2/redoc#tag/Dynamic-Association-Endpoints" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">[API Docs]</a>
        </div>
        <a href={`${base}/assets/GTEx Poster Hi-Res.pdf`} target="_blank">
          <img src={`${base}/assets/gtex.png`} alt="GTEx project poster" style="max-width: 120px; border-radius: 4px;" data-no-zoom />
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .bio-layout {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .bio-text {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .bio-img {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .project-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .bio-layout {
      flex-direction: column-reverse;
    }

    .bio-img img {
      max-width: 100% !important;
    }

    .project-card {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
